  <a href=http://pub7.ezboard.com/faegiswolvestunarepack.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=561.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nagafen update</span><hr size=1> I have another *really important* thing to add regarding lag/framerate.<br>
<br>
Before you go in, make sure you do the following things:<br>
<br>
Turn off particle effects<br>
<br>
Turn on server side filtering<br>
<br>
Turn off others hits, others misses, bard songs (except maybe group), npc spells, and possibly pc spells<br>
<br>
Turning off PC names helps a lot too, and generally, with the /target command you never need them.<br>
<br>
If your framerate is still bad and you are a caster, try facing away from the creature that is being attacked.  Especially for nukers, it isn't important to be actually looking at the creature during the fight.  Just make sure you turn around in time to see it die <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
Any other options I'm not thinking of that you can set to as low detail as possible, do.  The problem is twofold: network latency (lag) and framerate.  These two really aren't related to each other.  Putting 40-some people in a 10 foot radius of one another all doing their thing at full force generates more problems than you can imagine if you aren't prepared for it.  Even if you have a cable modem and never ever have lag problems, the amount of visual data can kill your framerate.  If you happen to have a 1300 MHz P4 with a Geforce3 and a Cable modem that never has lag for any reason, send me a tell if you're single, and ignore this post <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#FFFF00>- </font><a href=http://pub7.ezboard.com/baegiswolves>Aegis Wolves</a><font color=#FFFF00> - </font><a href=http://pub7.ezboard.com/faegiswolvestunarepack>Wolves Den - Tunare</a> <font color=#FFFF00> - </font><a href="www.mr-bandwidth.com/aegiswolves/">Home</a><font color=#FFFF00> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.6.4<br>Copyright ©1999-2001 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  